ns were involved in the crash, which led to the death of a person(passerby) and five people were unhurt. “The corpse of the victim was deposited at the morgue of General Hospital, Ifo, “he said.Umar attributed the unfortunate accident to mechanical deficiency, speeding and brake failure of the truck. He said the truck rammed into two other vehicles,  hitting the passerby and plunged into the river. The FRSC Officer advised motorists to always get their vehicles in good condition before putting them on the highways.He also cautioned them against excessive speed that could lead to loss of lives on the highways. Vanguard News Nigeria    5 die, 9 injured in Lagos-Ibadan expressway accident In "News" Eleven persons lost their lives to a  multiple auto crash near Isara Bridge, Ogere, off the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway on Saturday night. In "News" 7 die, 100 injured in 41 crashes during Sallah in Ogun – FRSC In "News"